-- Saudi Arabia Has 2 Million Sacks of Flour in Stock, Madina Says
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-04-10T05:50:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/saudi-arabia-has-2-million-sacks-of-flour-in-stock-madina-says.html
Saudi Arabia  has 2 million sacks of
flour in stock, or enough for six months’ consumption, in the
kingdom’s strategic wheat reserves,  al-Madina  newspaper
reported, citing Agriculture Minister Fahad Balghunaim.  Saudi Arabia has no plans to expand rice production because
it consumes large quantities of water, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  